{"word":"χάραξ","slug":"χάραξ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χάραξ</b></el> <el>(χάραξ, ακος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>χᾰράσσω</el>\n<p/><i>a pointed stake</i>: <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a>,<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a vine-prop</i> or <i>pole</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a pale</i>, used in entrenchments, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>collectively, = <a href='S:χαράκωμα'><el>χαράκωμα</el></a> II, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Polybius'>Polyb.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}